WEBVTT

00:02.001 --> 00:05.004
[adventurous music]

00:05.088 --> 00:12.095
♪ ♪

00:39.456 --> 00:40.915
- YAY!

00:40.999 --> 00:42.959
- HELLO!

00:43.042 --> 00:44.002
- WHERE'S JOY?

00:44.085 --> 00:45.211
- OH, IS NINA HERE?

00:45.295 --> 00:46.421
- OH, THEY'RE BOTH
ON THEIR WAY.

00:46.504 --> 00:49.132
OH, I'M LOVING
TO SEE YOU ALL.

00:49.215 --> 00:50.133
NOW, GO UPSTAIRS.

00:50.216 --> 00:51.301
I'VE BEEN BAKING ALL DAY.

00:51.384 --> 00:52.969
- OH, YES!

00:53.052 --> 00:55.805
- OOH, AMBER, LET ME HELP YOU.

00:55.889 --> 00:58.308
OOH, YOU'VE BROUGHT
ENOUGH LUGGAGE, HAVE YOU?

00:58.391 --> 00:59.100
- OH, THESE ARE JUST MY SHOES.

00:59.184 --> 01:01.186
ACTUALLY, JUST MY WEDGES.

01:01.269 --> 01:03.271
THE REST ARE IN THE DRIVE.

01:03.354 --> 01:04.897
THANKS, TRUDES.

01:07.442 --> 01:09.402
[ominous music]

01:09.486 --> 01:15.450
♪ ♪

01:30.507 --> 01:31.716
- JEROME?

01:32.842 --> 01:33.760
- NINA, HELLO.

01:33.843 --> 01:35.261
WELCOME BACK.

01:42.477 --> 01:43.645
UGH!

01:57.784 --> 01:59.702
- HEY!
- AH!

01:59.786 --> 02:03.623
ALFIE, DON'T DO THAT.

02:03.706 --> 02:06.042
IF YOU'RE LOST,
THE '80s ARE THAT WAY.

02:06.125 --> 02:07.377
- IT'S FOR AMBER.

02:07.460 --> 02:08.544
NEW TERM, NEW GIRLFRIEND...

02:08.627 --> 02:10.713
NEW ALFIE.

02:11.631 --> 02:13.633
- OH!

02:13.716 --> 02:15.218
- AGAIN, AGAIN.

02:15.301 --> 02:17.178
- JOY!

02:17.262 --> 02:19.097
- OH, IT'S SO GOOD
TO BE BACK.

02:19.180 --> 02:19.681
- IT'S GOOD TO HAVE YOU BACK,
JOY.

02:19.764 --> 02:21.724
- THANKS, FABES.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.101
AND YOU TWO!

02:23.184 --> 02:25.395
I DIDN'T SEE
THAT ONE COMING.

02:25.478 --> 02:26.980
- OH, I KNOW.
THE ATHLETE...

02:27.063 --> 02:28.731
- AND THE MATH-LETE.

02:28.815 --> 02:30.817
- SHE CAN'T RUN,
AND HE CAN'T ADD UP.

02:30.900 --> 02:34.070
[laughter]

02:42.829 --> 02:46.624
[ominous music]

02:52.589 --> 02:53.840
- FABIAN GOT THE BROWNIES.

02:53.923 --> 02:55.216
- HEY, NINA!

02:55.300 --> 02:56.801
- NINA!

02:56.885 --> 02:58.261
- HI!

02:58.344 --> 02:59.554
- HEY.

02:59.637 --> 03:01.014
- SO HOW ARE YOU?

03:01.097 --> 03:02.348
- STILL AMERICAN?

03:02.432 --> 03:04.434
- YEP.
STILL PATRICIA?

03:04.517 --> 03:06.311
[laughter]

03:08.271 --> 03:09.522
HEY.

03:09.606 --> 03:11.190
- HEY.

03:11.274 --> 03:12.317
- OKAY.

03:12.400 --> 03:14.611
TIME TO MAKE A DISCREET EXIT,
EVERYONE.

03:14.694 --> 03:16.487
- DO YOU WANT TO COME
AND SET UP YOUR ROOM, JOY?

03:16.571 --> 03:17.697
WE SHARE WITH MARA NOW.

03:17.780 --> 03:19.824
- WHAT'S WRONG
WITH OUR OLD ROOM?

03:21.868 --> 03:24.495
- SO, UM...

03:24.579 --> 03:25.538
HOW WAS YOUR FLIGHT?

03:25.622 --> 03:27.040
- GOOD.
AND YOU?

03:27.123 --> 03:29.626
- I CAME BY CAR.

03:29.709 --> 03:30.168
- [laughs]
YEAH.

03:30.251 --> 03:33.421
I MEAN, UM...

03:33.504 --> 03:34.881
NEVER MIND.

03:36.215 --> 03:38.760
[door opens]
- DO YOU MIND?

03:38.843 --> 03:40.094
PEOPLE ARE EATING IN HERE.

03:40.178 --> 03:42.055
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

03:42.138 --> 03:43.598
[sighs]

03:53.566 --> 03:56.736
- THEY HAVE RETURNED, CORBIERE.

03:56.819 --> 03:59.322
OUR PRECIOUS PEACE
IS SHATTERED ONCE MORE.

04:24.263 --> 04:25.890
- TAKE IT.

04:25.974 --> 04:26.849
HIDE IT.

04:26.933 --> 04:29.644
KEEP IT SAFE.

04:33.731 --> 04:35.108
[door opens]

04:39.988 --> 04:42.156
- IS SOMEBODY IN HERE?

05:07.807 --> 05:09.183
- HEY, I WONDERED
WHERE YOU WERE.

05:09.267 --> 05:11.185
- I JUST HAD TO FIX SOMETHING
DOWN AT THE SCHOOL.

05:11.269 --> 05:12.895
- OKAY?

05:12.979 --> 05:14.564
YOU SURE?

05:20.153 --> 05:22.405
- IT'S ALL VERY COUPLY.

05:22.488 --> 05:24.407
- YOU'RE NOT WRONG THERE, JOY.

05:24.490 --> 05:26.242
- UH, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

05:26.325 --> 05:27.952
- UH, BEING COUPLY.

05:28.036 --> 05:31.789
- SO GO HOLD HIS HAND.

05:31.873 --> 05:33.291
- YOUR LAST MAIL
MENTIONED SOMETHING

05:33.374 --> 05:35.084
ABOUT YOUR GRANDMOTHER
COMING OUT?

05:35.168 --> 05:36.085
- MM, YEAH, YEAH.

05:36.169 --> 05:37.253
SHE'S COMING TO VISIT.

05:37.336 --> 05:38.713
SHE'S STAYING
AT A HOTEL IN TOWN.

05:38.796 --> 05:40.590
SHE'S REALLY EXCITED
TO MEET YOU ALL.

05:40.673 --> 05:41.424
ESPECIALLY YOU.

05:41.507 --> 05:42.550
I TOLD HER A LOT ABOUT YOU.

05:42.633 --> 05:45.219
- YEAH, WE DO BREED
BETTER GEEKS OVER HERE.

05:45.303 --> 05:47.305
[laughter]

05:48.598 --> 05:51.517
- SIBUNA REUNION,
MIDNIGHT FEAST IN THE ATTIC.

05:51.601 --> 05:52.185
PASS IT ON.

05:52.268 --> 05:55.271
[cell phone ringing]

05:55.354 --> 05:57.106
- GOT POPULAR PHONES.

05:57.190 --> 05:57.940
WHO'S POOPY?

05:58.024 --> 06:01.444
- DEH--MY...LIFE COACH.

06:01.527 --> 06:03.446
[ringing continues]

06:08.659 --> 06:12.246
- IT'S 10:00.

06:12.330 --> 06:14.957
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.

06:15.041 --> 06:18.294
YOU HAVE FIVE MINUTES PRECISELY,

06:18.377 --> 06:24.842
AND THEN I WANT TO HEAR
A PIN DROP.

06:24.926 --> 06:27.136
[gentle clanging]

06:37.563 --> 06:39.690
- DO WE HAVE ANYTHING
TO PICK THE LOCK?

06:39.774 --> 06:40.191
[door opening]

06:40.274 --> 06:42.401
[all gasp]

06:42.485 --> 06:44.112
[door creaking]

06:44.195 --> 06:47.448
- WHOA.

06:47.532 --> 06:49.742
WELCOME BACK
TO CREEPY TOWERS.

06:49.826 --> 06:52.787
- MAYBE THIS MIDNIGHT FEAST
SHOULD TAKE PLACE IN DAYLIGHT.

06:52.870 --> 06:54.789
GOOD NIGHT.

07:14.517 --> 07:17.520
-<i> ELIXIR VITAE.</i>

07:17.603 --> 07:19.564
WATER OF LIFE.

07:23.234 --> 07:23.484
MM!

07:25.736 --> 07:26.028
[spits]

07:26.112 --> 07:28.197
UGH!

07:46.924 --> 07:48.259
[gags]

07:48.342 --> 07:51.262
[glass shatters]

07:51.345 --> 07:52.597
- SIBUNA, EVERYBODY.

07:52.680 --> 07:53.764
WELCOME BACK.

07:53.848 --> 07:54.891
all: SIBUNA.

07:54.974 --> 07:56.934
- NO TROUBLE
GETTING PAST VICTOR, THEN?

07:57.018 --> 07:58.352
- NO, HE WASN'T IN HIS OFFICE.

07:58.436 --> 07:59.729
MAYBE HE'S FINALLY
CHANGED HIS WAYS

07:59.812 --> 08:01.564
AND GONE TO BED EARLY.

08:01.647 --> 08:03.316
- WELL, HE NEEDS
HIS BEAUTY SLEEP.

08:03.399 --> 08:05.818
HE IS 101.

08:05.902 --> 08:08.946
- TALKING ABOUT CREEPS
OBSESSED WITH LIVING FOREVER,

08:09.030 --> 08:13.951
YOU GUYS WILL BE INTERESTED
IN THIS.

08:14.035 --> 08:15.953
- IT'S AN OBITUARY
FOR RENE ZELDMAN.

08:16.037 --> 08:18.873
- RUFUS.

08:18.956 --> 08:22.835
- I GUESS HE FOUND OUT
HE WASN'T IMMORTAL THE HARD WAY.

08:22.919 --> 08:24.212
[soda can opens]
[girl screeches]

08:24.295 --> 08:26.255
- ALFIE!

08:26.339 --> 08:29.050
[clattering]
[ominous music]

08:29.133 --> 08:29.759
- WHAT WAS THAT?

08:29.842 --> 08:31.510
- SOMEONE'S COMING.

08:36.182 --> 08:37.475
- JOY!

08:37.558 --> 08:39.227
YOU SCARED US TO DEATH.

08:39.309 --> 08:42.355
- GUYS, THEY'RE IN HERE.

08:45.107 --> 08:46.525
- NICE HANGOUT, GUYS.

08:46.609 --> 08:49.779
- I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE HAVING
AN ANUBIS MIDNIGHT REUNION

08:49.862 --> 08:53.741
AND YOU DIDN'T INVITE US.

08:53.824 --> 08:55.201
- SURPRISE!

08:55.284 --> 08:58.621
[all cheering]

08:58.704 --> 08:59.997
WE WANTED TO WELCOME YOU BACK
PROPERLY.

09:00.081 --> 09:02.208
- UP HERE?

09:02.291 --> 09:03.876
- YEAH.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.002
- WHILE I'M ASLEEP.

09:05.086 --> 09:05.795
- WELL, Y-YEAH.

09:05.878 --> 09:08.923
ARE YOU SURPRISED, OR WHAT?

09:09.006 --> 09:10.758
- UH, I'LL JUST GET
ANOTHER SHEET.

09:18.432 --> 09:20.559
WOW.

09:28.067 --> 09:33.155
- ETERNAL LIFE SHALL BE MINE
ONE DAY, CORBIERE.

09:33.239 --> 09:36.617
BUT I STILL NEED THAT ELIXIR.

09:36.701 --> 09:38.703
[thuds, shouting]

09:42.456 --> 09:44.583
- OW! OW! OW!
MY TOE!

09:44.667 --> 09:45.209
- SORRY.
IT WAS HEAVY.

09:45.293 --> 09:48.337
- SHUSH, YOU TWO.

09:48.421 --> 09:51.424
- I ALWAYS WANTED A DOLL HOUSE.

09:51.507 --> 09:54.885
- EVEN ONE THAT'S A REPLICA
OF A CREEPY OLD ANUBIS HOUSE?

09:56.721 --> 09:58.347
- WHERE DOLLIES GO TO DIE.

09:58.431 --> 09:59.682
[laughter]

10:11.777 --> 10:17.241
- WHOEVER IS UP THERE,
COME DOWN IMMEDIATELY!

10:17.325 --> 10:18.659
DID YOU HEAR
WHAT I JUST SAID?

10:29.962 --> 10:31.797
GO TO YOUR ROOMS IMMEDIATELY.

10:31.881 --> 10:35.885
WE SHALL DEAL WITH YOUR
PUNISHMENT IN THE MORNING.

10:35.968 --> 10:37.178
COME ALONG!

10:42.350 --> 10:44.602
- SOMEONE MISSING.

10:44.685 --> 10:45.311
NINA MARTIN...

10:45.394 --> 10:48.105
ARE YOU UP THERE TOO?

10:48.189 --> 10:51.984
[chiming]

10:54.153 --> 10:55.571
WELL...

11:08.834 --> 11:10.002
- AH!

11:10.086 --> 11:12.338
- WHAT ARE YOU PLAYING AT?

11:25.142 --> 11:27.228
- AH!

11:27.311 --> 11:29.480
- WHAT ARE YOU PLAYING AT?

11:30.773 --> 11:33.150
JUST LOOK WHAT YOU'VE DONE.

11:33.234 --> 11:35.486
GET OUT.

11:35.569 --> 11:36.946
GET OUT!

11:48.207 --> 11:49.583
- THE ATHENAEUM
IS THE PLACE TO LOOK.

11:49.667 --> 11:52.962
LIFT THE WINGS TO FIND THE BOOK.

11:53.045 --> 11:53.963
HIDDEN IN THIS BOOK OF OLD,

11:54.046 --> 11:57.133
WATER OF LIFE
AND TEARS OF GOLD.

11:57.216 --> 11:57.758
- "WATER OF LIFE."

12:05.891 --> 12:07.977
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN YOU CAN'T
REMEMBER OUR ARRANGEMENT?

12:08.060 --> 12:11.063
- I DON'T MAKE ARRANGEMENTS
MORE THAN 48 HOURS IN ADVANCE,

12:11.147 --> 12:12.481
UNLESS IT'S SPONTANEOUS.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.316
- BUT YOU PROMISED YOU'D BE
MY GIRLFRIEND LAST TERM.

12:14.400 --> 12:15.109
I HAVE WITNESSES.

12:15.192 --> 12:16.819
- HEARD IT WITH MY OWN EARS.

12:16.902 --> 12:18.112
- ME TOO.

12:18.195 --> 12:20.322
- PATRICIA, JOY,
HELP ME OUT HERE.

12:20.406 --> 12:24.493
- ACTUALLY, AMBER,
YOU DID SAY THAT.

12:24.577 --> 12:25.327
- YES, OKAY, BUT...

12:25.411 --> 12:27.538
I THOUGHT HE WAS DYING.

12:27.621 --> 12:31.333
THAT'S WHAT DADDY
CALLS A LOOPHOLE.

12:31.417 --> 12:33.335
PATRICIA, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

12:33.419 --> 12:34.753
- YEAH, COME ON, JUDGE TRIXIE.

12:34.837 --> 12:36.464
- OKAY, NO.

12:36.547 --> 12:38.174
AMBER DIDN'T QUITE SAY THAT.

12:38.257 --> 12:39.425
- THANK YOU.

12:39.508 --> 12:42.303
- WHAT SHE ACTUALLY SAID WAS,

12:42.386 --> 12:45.014
"YES, YES, YES, ANYTHING."

12:45.097 --> 12:46.390
- THANK YOU, YOUR HONOR.

12:46.474 --> 12:47.516
- THANKS A BUNCH.

12:47.600 --> 12:48.934
SO MUCH FOR THE SISTERHOOD.

12:49.018 --> 12:50.019
- IN THERE, PLEASE.

12:50.102 --> 12:51.395
I WANT A WORD WITH ALL OF YOU.

12:51.479 --> 12:54.106
SIT DOWN, PLEASE.
SIT.

12:54.190 --> 12:56.901
SO...
FIRST NIGHT BACK,

12:56.984 --> 13:00.863
AND ALREADY YOU ARE
UP TO NO GOOD.

13:00.946 --> 13:06.035
WELL, I SHALL NOT STAND
FOR YOUR NONSENSE THIS TERM.

13:06.118 --> 13:08.162
DO YOU HEAR ME?

13:08.245 --> 13:09.246
WELL?

13:09.330 --> 13:13.209
- YES, VICTOR.

13:13.292 --> 13:15.085
- WAIT, DOES THIS MEAN

13:15.169 --> 13:17.630
ALL OF US
CLEANING ONE TOILET?

13:17.713 --> 13:20.257
- NO, MR. CAMPBELL, NO.

13:20.341 --> 13:21.926
IT MEANS ALL OF YOU

13:22.009 --> 13:27.223
CLEANING EVERY SINGLE TOILET
IN THE ENTIRE SCHOOL.

13:27.306 --> 13:31.477
- THIS IS A £50 MANICURE,
I'LL HAVE YOU KNOW.

13:31.560 --> 13:33.395
- HE'S DEFINITELY MISSED US.

13:35.272 --> 13:37.274
- IT SAID SOMETHING ABOUT
"WATER OF LIFE"

13:37.358 --> 13:37.983
AND "TEARS OF GOLD"

13:38.067 --> 13:39.068
AND SOME "BOOK OF OLD"

13:39.151 --> 13:44.365
WHICH CAN BE FOUND
IN AN "ATHENAEUM"?

13:44.448 --> 13:45.616
- I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT "TEARS OF GOLD,"

13:45.699 --> 13:48.994
BUT AN "ATHENAEUM"
IS ANOTHER WORD FOR "LIBRARY."

13:49.078 --> 13:52.206
- SUPER USEFUL,
DATING A WORD NERD.

13:52.289 --> 13:54.208
- AND YOU CAN GUESS
WHAT "WATER OF LIFE" MEANS.

13:54.291 --> 13:56.585
- YEAH, THE ELIXIR.

13:56.669 --> 13:57.545
- HEY, GUYS.

13:57.628 --> 13:58.754
MICK AND I ARE GOING
INTO TOWN

13:58.837 --> 13:59.338
TOMORROW NIGHT
TO CATCH A MOVIE.

13:59.421 --> 14:01.215
WANT TO COME?

14:01.298 --> 14:03.175
- YEAH, SOUNDS GREAT.
HMM?

14:03.259 --> 14:04.468
- SURE.

14:07.054 --> 14:09.265
- AH, FINALLY, A PROPER DATE.

14:09.348 --> 14:13.227
AND THIS TIME, NO EVIL MANIACS
OR POISONOUS FLIES.

14:13.310 --> 14:14.478
- HEY, JEROME.

14:25.531 --> 14:28.867
- UH, JOY...

14:28.951 --> 14:30.494
- OH, IS THIS...

14:30.578 --> 14:31.453
- YEAH.

14:31.537 --> 14:33.789
- WE USED TO SHARE.

14:33.872 --> 14:34.248
I FORGOT.

14:34.331 --> 14:36.625
I'LL...

14:43.048 --> 14:44.466
FIRST MY ROOM,
AND THEN MY FABIAN.

14:44.550 --> 14:46.885
WHAT'S NEXT?

14:46.969 --> 14:47.428
MY MUM?
MY CAT?

14:47.511 --> 14:48.637
MY FREEDOM?

14:48.721 --> 14:51.307
- JOY, YOU AND FABIAN

14:51.390 --> 14:54.518
WERE NEVER ACTUALLY GOING OUT.

14:54.602 --> 14:55.853
- MORNING.

14:55.936 --> 14:57.646
all: MORNING, MRS. ANDREWS.

14:57.730 --> 15:01.150
- RIGHT.
UH, WORLD LITERATURE.

15:01.233 --> 15:05.154
FAIRY TALES AND FOLK STORIES.

15:05.237 --> 15:06.614
SO WILL YOU HAND THESE OUT?

15:06.697 --> 15:08.866
PAGE 22, PLEASE.

15:08.949 --> 15:09.992
- ONCE UPON A TIME,

15:10.075 --> 15:11.577
THERE WAS A POOR BOY
NAMED ALFREDO

15:11.660 --> 15:12.745
WHO FELL IN LOVE
WITH A BEAUTIFUL

15:12.828 --> 15:14.038
BUT VERY CHOOSY PRINCESS.

15:14.121 --> 15:17.666
THE PRINCESS
MADE ALFREDO A PROMISE, BUT...

15:17.750 --> 15:21.337
- I DID NOT PROMISE.

15:21.420 --> 15:23.505
AND ANYWAY,
I TOOK YOU TO THE PROM.

15:23.589 --> 15:25.090
NO ONE CAN SAY
I DON'T GIVE BACK.

15:30.262 --> 15:32.306
-<i> THE AMBER MILLINGTON</i>
<i>GUIDE TO DATING.</i>

15:32.389 --> 15:33.807
- TAKE A LOOK AT THAT,
AND YOU'LL SEE

15:33.891 --> 15:36.435
WHY WE CAN NEVER BE
AM-FIE OR AL-BER.

15:36.518 --> 15:37.102
SEE?
IT DOESN'T EVEN SOUND RIGHT.

15:43.067 --> 15:45.027
- ATHENAEUM
IS THE PLACE TO LOOK.

15:45.110 --> 15:48.197
LIFT THE WINGS
TO FIND THE BOOK.

15:48.280 --> 15:49.198
HIDDEN IN THIS BOOK OF OLD,

15:49.281 --> 15:52.409
WATER OF LIFE
AND TEARS OF GOLD.

15:52.493 --> 15:56.330
- IT USED TO BELONG
TO THE DAUGHTER OF THE HOUSE.

15:56.413 --> 15:59.041
- SARAH FROBISHER-SMYTHE.

15:59.124 --> 16:00.542
- NOW DO YOU SEE
ITS SIGNIFICANCE?

16:00.626 --> 16:04.046
- THE BOOK OF OLD.

16:04.129 --> 16:06.215
DIDN'T YOUR FATHER
USED TO REFER TO THAT AS--

16:06.298 --> 16:08.801
- THE BOOK OF ISIS, YES.

16:08.884 --> 16:12.262
- AND YOU THINK IT CONTAINS
THE ELIXIR RECIPE?

16:14.348 --> 16:18.185
AND THE TEARS OF GOLD?

16:18.268 --> 16:23.732
- PERHAPS THE MISSING
ELIXIR INGREDIENT.

16:23.816 --> 16:28.987
AND I THINK I KNOW
WHERE TO FIND THIS BOOK.

16:29.071 --> 16:32.324
- HOMEWORK IN
BY NEXT FRIDAY, PLEASE.

16:32.408 --> 16:35.619
- "ONE: GIFTS.
HE MUST SHOWER ME WITH THEM.

16:35.703 --> 16:37.121
"TWO: HOTNESS.

16:37.204 --> 16:40.082
"HE MUST BE HOT ENOUGH
TO GET ON A MAGAZINE COVER.

16:40.165 --> 16:41.125
"AND THREE: WHEELS.

16:41.208 --> 16:45.212
HE MUST, MUST, MUST
HAVE A SET."

16:45.295 --> 16:46.088
- AND BEFORE YOU TRY, ALFIE,

16:46.171 --> 16:47.423
IT DOESN'T MEAN SKATEBOARD.

16:47.506 --> 16:50.259
- SO IF I GET THE WHEELS,
THE GIFTS, AND COVER SHOT,

16:50.342 --> 16:51.343
THEN YOU'LL GO OUT WITH ME?

16:51.427 --> 16:52.761
- YES, ALFIE,

16:52.845 --> 16:54.513
IN THE UNLIKELY EVENT
YOU ACHEIVE ALL THOSE THINGS,

16:54.596 --> 16:55.556
I WILL GO OUT WITH YOU.

16:55.639 --> 16:56.974
- PIECE OF CAKE.

17:04.690 --> 17:06.608
- THAT ONE.

17:06.692 --> 17:09.028
I LOVE YOU IN THAT SHIRT.

17:09.111 --> 17:10.028
- NINA?

17:10.112 --> 17:11.488
- THIS ONE.

17:11.571 --> 17:13.615
- I LIKE THE WAY YOU'RE SMILING
STRAIGHT AT THE CAMERA.

17:13.699 --> 17:14.616
NICE EYES.

17:14.700 --> 17:16.785
- NO WAY.

17:16.868 --> 17:18.662
PATRICIA, TELL HIM.

17:18.746 --> 17:22.875
- I THINK HE LOOKS LIKE A DORK
IN ALL OF THEM.

17:22.958 --> 17:25.919
HEY, IT STILL SAYS
YOU'RE SINGLE, FABIAN.

17:26.002 --> 17:28.005
- UH, SORRY.
I'LL CHANGE THAT.

17:28.088 --> 17:29.590
SORRY.

17:33.385 --> 17:36.305
- I'M GETTING SERIOUSLY WORRIED
ABOUT JEROME.

17:36.388 --> 17:36.722
- REALLY?

17:36.805 --> 17:38.682
- SO...

17:38.766 --> 17:40.851
COULD YOU GO OUT WITH ME
TO TAKE MY MIND OFF IT?

17:44.271 --> 17:45.314
all: HI, JEROME.

17:51.737 --> 17:53.864
- [sighs]
THANK YOU.

17:53.947 --> 17:58.118
- ANYONE WOULD THINK
YOU'RE TRYING TO AVOID ME.

17:58.202 --> 18:00.829
BIG MISTAKE.

18:00.913 --> 18:03.957
IF YOU WANT TO BUY MY SILENCE,

18:04.041 --> 18:07.336
HERE'S A LIST OF MY DEMANDS.

18:07.419 --> 18:09.713
SAME TIME TOMORROW, CLARKE.

18:17.554 --> 18:22.601
- SO DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S UP WITH YOU?

18:22.684 --> 18:23.936
- ME?

18:24.019 --> 18:25.896
I'M JUST WONDERING
WHEN YOU'RE GONNA GIVE UP

18:25.979 --> 18:27.189
ON PRINCESS PUSHY?

18:27.272 --> 18:29.441
- OH, WELL, I NEED
TO FIND THE PERFECT GIFT.

18:29.525 --> 18:31.443
DO YOU THINK
SHE'LL PREFER FLOWERS

18:31.527 --> 18:34.196
OR AN ADOPTION CERTIFICATE
FOR A BABY VULTURE?

18:36.782 --> 18:37.825
- IF YOU DON'T KNOW
THE ANSWER TO THAT,

18:37.908 --> 18:39.618
YOU'RE GOING
TO BE SINGLE FOREVER.

18:39.701 --> 18:42.538
[knock on door]

18:42.621 --> 18:45.374
- ALFIE, DO YOU STILL WANT HELP
WITH THOSE CUPCAKES?

18:45.457 --> 18:46.875
- OH, YEAH, COMING.

18:46.959 --> 18:48.836
- CUPCAKES?

18:48.919 --> 18:50.504
- LET THE GIFT SHOWER BEGIN.

18:50.587 --> 18:52.631
TONIGHT IT'S RAINING CUPCAKES.

18:52.714 --> 18:54.550
UH, COULD YOU CHOOSE
SOME FLOWERS FOR ME, DUDE?

18:54.633 --> 18:56.802
THINK A BIG GESTURE, YEAH?

19:02.099 --> 19:04.726
- ORCHIDS?
THAT'S FAR TOO SAFE.

19:04.810 --> 19:08.021
PICK SOMETHING A LITTLE EDGIER.

19:08.105 --> 19:09.940
[laughs]

19:10.023 --> 19:12.651
- HERE IT IS,
THE FROBISHER LIBRARY.

19:12.734 --> 19:13.735
IT'S BEEN CLOSED
SINCE THE '70s.

19:13.819 --> 19:15.779
I ALWAYS WONDERED
WHAT WAS IN THERE.

19:18.407 --> 19:19.741
WHAT?

19:19.825 --> 19:21.785
- JUST MIGHT HAVE KNOWN
YOUR ROMANTIC STROLL

19:21.869 --> 19:25.706
WOULD LEAD US
TO A HAUNTED LIBRARY.

19:25.789 --> 19:28.000
THINK THIS IS THE LIBRARY
FROM THE RIDDLE?

19:28.083 --> 19:29.751
- IF THE DOLL IS AS OLD
AS YOU SAY IT IS,

19:29.835 --> 19:31.461
THEN THE LIBRARY
WE USE IN SCHOOL

19:31.545 --> 19:31.879
WASN'T EVEN BUILT,

19:31.962 --> 19:34.339
SO YEAH.

19:41.346 --> 19:42.472
IT'S OPEN.

19:42.556 --> 19:43.724
DID YOUR LOCKET DO THAT?

19:43.807 --> 19:44.308
- NOT GUILTY.

19:47.477 --> 19:50.439
[suspenseful music]

19:50.522 --> 19:51.648
♪ ♪

19:51.732 --> 19:55.360
- NINA...

19:55.444 --> 19:56.778
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:03.201 --> 20:06.705
- WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR
EXACTLY, VICTOR?

20:06.788 --> 20:11.335
- PRESS THE WINGS
TO FIND THE BOOK.

20:13.420 --> 20:14.546
- RIDDLE.

20:14.630 --> 20:17.174
- THE GODDESS ISIS IS DEPICTED
AS HAVING WINGS.

20:17.257 --> 20:22.137
PERHAPS SOME KIND OF ENGRAVING
OR CARVING.

20:22.221 --> 20:24.139
- COULD BE ANYTHING.

20:24.222 --> 20:26.934
WHAT ABOUT ON ONE
OF THESE BOOKSHELVES?

20:29.603 --> 20:31.021
- I THINK IT HIGHLY UNLIKELY

20:31.104 --> 20:32.648
THAT ROBERT FROBISHER-SMYTHE

20:32.731 --> 20:37.819
WOULD HIDE THE BOOK OF ISIS
ON A BOOKSHELF.

20:37.903 --> 20:40.364
PERHAPS UP HERE?

20:40.447 --> 20:43.867
PRESS THE WINGS...

20:43.951 --> 20:47.663
TO FIND THE BOOK.

20:47.746 --> 20:51.416
PRESS...

20:51.500 --> 20:54.670
THE WINGS...

20:54.753 --> 20:57.422
TO FIND THE BOOK.

21:01.718 --> 21:03.929
ERIC!

21:06.932 --> 21:08.183
NO!

21:08.266 --> 21:10.852
IT'S GONE!

21:10.936 --> 21:13.313
THE BOOK OF ISIS IS GONE.

21:16.525 --> 21:21.154
THE RECIPE FOR THE ELIXIR
ELUDES ME STILL.

21:21.238 --> 21:23.740
- PERHAPS WE SHOULD
JUST FACE THE TRUTH, VICTOR.

21:23.824 --> 21:24.533
THE ELIXIR IS FINISHED.

21:24.616 --> 21:26.702
THE CUP HAS BEEN DESTROYED.

21:26.785 --> 21:28.495
AND IT'S OVER.

21:28.578 --> 21:29.871
YOU SAID SO YOURSELF.

21:29.955 --> 21:31.790
- IF WE HAD THE ELIXIR, ERIC,

21:31.873 --> 21:33.583
IT WOULD BUY US TIME.

21:33.667 --> 21:35.877
AND WITH TIME,
ALTERNATIVE SOLUTIONS

21:35.961 --> 21:37.421
MAY PRESENT THEMSELVES.

21:37.504 --> 21:38.296
[books clattering]
